Disclaimer: I worked here '95-'98   I love Himal Chuli.
Bishnu and Jamuna has been making some of the best food in the world (to me) "with love" for many years.
They would always tell me that was why it was so good - because she cooked "with love" ;) I have noticed their proces have risen dramatically, but that will not keep me from eating there when I am in town.
It is hard to say what the "best" menu item is, because everything is sooooo incredibly good.
A few of my favorites are the daal (yellow lentil soup), daily takari (vegetarian stew) and roti (yoghurt leavened flatbread), the chicken or tofu polungo (lightly breaded chicken with a tomato based sauce containing spinach and mushrooms), the momo/momcha (dumplings), chicken sikar (fall-off-the-bone chicken and sauce), beef buff (beef with cumin/coriander, sauted with broccoli)... and really I dont think there is a single thing I dont like on the menu!
Get some golub jamun and a lasi for desert ;)

